HEADWORD: Sedimentation
<hw>Sed`i*men*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
depositing a sediment; specifically <fld>(Geol.)</fld>, the deposition
of the material of which sedimentary rocks are formed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sedition</ent>⟦br⟧
